  "body": "This is from the new performance test in #2501 - it takes almost 1.5s for `Array.from(readonlyValues(aggregationBits))`\r\n<img width=\"1460\" alt=\"statusProcessEpoch2\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10568965/117744292-9a31dc80-b232-11eb-860c-0497e90c199e.png\">\r\n(notice that the statistic is 1 line shift to the downside somehow)\r\n\r\nCurrently for  `readonlyValues` of BitList, we return an iterator by yielding each separate bit and then the consumer (lodestar) aggregate them again as `boolean[]`.\r\n\r\nWe should be able to write an util to access the respective chunks and the consumer can just use that.",
